00:12:18.820 --> 00:12:21.150 align:middle line:90%


00:12:21.150 --> 00:12:26.360 align:middle line:84%
>> So this is the [INAUDIBLE],,
although it's not a great

00:12:26.360 --> 00:12:27.620 align:middle line:90%
likeness of him.

00:12:27.620 --> 00:12:30.410 align:middle line:84%
But what this room
does is give us

00:12:30.410 --> 00:12:33.950 align:middle line:84%
a place to focus our
gratitude to Suzuki Roshi.

00:12:33.950 --> 00:12:36.210 align:middle line:90%
That's the point of this room.

00:12:36.210 --> 00:12:39.860 align:middle line:84%
He was in this room
as he was dying

00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:46.460 align:middle line:84%
so that he would be
available to the students,

00:12:46.460 --> 00:12:53.100 align:middle line:84%
for them to see him and him to
see them, up until very soon

00:12:53.100 --> 00:12:53.900 align:middle line:90%
before he died.

00:12:53.900 --> 00:12:54.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Really?

00:12:54.690 --> 00:12:55.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:12:55.490 --> 00:12:57.440 align:middle line:84%
So we bow to him
each time we pass.

00:12:57.440 --> 00:13:01.080 align:middle line:90%


00:13:01.080 --> 00:13:05.670 align:middle line:84%
We're extremely fortunate
to have this building.

00:13:05.670 --> 00:13:10.230 align:middle line:10%
It was a Jewish residence
hall for young ladies

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:11.370 align:middle line:10%
away from their families.

00:13:11.370 --> 00:13:14.400 align:middle line:84%
Young ladies in the
'20s didn't live alone.

00:13:14.400 --> 00:13:17.130 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, this is
very famous for--

00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.390 align:middle line:90%
many matches were made here.

00:13:18.390 --> 00:13:21.512 align:middle line:84%
Because people have come
celebrating their 50th wedding

00:13:21.512 --> 00:13:23.220 align:middle line:84%
anniversary and bring
their grandchildren

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:26.520 align:middle line:84%
to show them where
Grandpa and Grandma met.

00:13:26.520 --> 00:13:31.410 align:middle line:84%
So this is our Zendo,
our meditation hall.

00:13:31.410 --> 00:13:34.350 align:middle line:90%
This is the ceremonial hall.

00:13:34.350 --> 00:13:37.380 align:middle line:84%
This is where we have
morning service every day

00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:40.020 align:middle line:84%
and any ceremonies that
we do-- ordinations,

00:13:40.020 --> 00:13:41.820 align:middle line:90%
funerals, weddings.

00:13:41.820 --> 00:13:45.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Today's Zen Center, as it's
called, is one of the largest,

00:13:45.580 --> 00:13:50.220 align:middle line:84%
if not the largest, Buddhist
organizations outside Asia.

00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:53.580 align:middle line:84%
The downtown property consists
of a number of buildings

00:13:53.580 --> 00:13:59.260 align:middle line:84%
and is home to between 45 and
65 residents at any given time.

00:13:59.260 --> 00:14:02.550 align:middle line:84%
As well, there's Tassajara
Monastic Center in the Ventana

00:14:02.550 --> 00:14:05.400 align:middle line:84%
Wilderness and the Green
Gulch Farm Practice

00:14:05.400 --> 00:14:06.765 align:middle line:90%
Center in Marin County.

00:14:06.765 --> 00:14:10.770 align:middle line:84%
>> I have to say that the
second abbot, Richard Baker,

00:14:10.770 --> 00:14:13.320 align:middle line:90%
did a lot to build Zen Center.

00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:14.770 align:middle line:90%
I never wanted him to leave.

00:14:14.770 --> 00:14:17.890 align:middle line:84%
I wanted him to say,
