00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:43.640 align:middle line:84%
Baker was forced to resign
in 1984 after a scandal that

00:14:43.640 --> 00:14:45.070 align:middle line:90%
rocked the community.

00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:47.840 align:middle line:90%
>> He was having--

00:14:47.840 --> 00:14:51.560 align:middle line:84%
consensual-- but he was
having sexual relationships

00:14:51.560 --> 00:14:52.670 align:middle line:90%
with students.

00:14:52.670 --> 00:14:58.213 align:middle line:84%
And people got really upset
about it, and appropriately so.

00:14:58.213 --> 00:14:59.630 align:middle line:84%
It's not appropriate
for a teacher

00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:01.925 align:middle line:84%
to have sexual
relationships with students.

00:15:01.925 --> 00:15:05.390 align:middle line:90%
>> And this is the Zendo here.

00:15:05.390 --> 00:15:08.390 align:middle line:84%
>> What was interesting from
the point of view of Buddhism

00:15:08.390 --> 00:15:12.200 align:middle line:84%
in the West was not the scandal,
but the effect on the budding

00:15:12.200 --> 00:15:16.010 align:middle line:84%
community and how they dealt
with its aftermath both

00:15:16.010 --> 00:15:18.785 align:middle line:84%
psychologically and
organizationally.

00:15:18.785 --> 00:15:22.720 align:middle line:84%
>> It was the
death of innocence.

00:15:22.720 --> 00:15:35.310 align:middle line:84%
We had a kind of faith that
was naive and unrealistic.

00:15:35.310 --> 00:15:39.250 align:middle line:84%
And so when it all
happened and we kind of

00:15:39.250 --> 00:15:41.800 align:middle line:84%
realized that the person we
had faith in and that we had

00:15:41.800 --> 00:15:46.640 align:middle line:84%
projected was not the person
that was actually there,

00:15:46.640 --> 00:15:50.340 align:middle line:84%
it was enormously disturbing
on a lot of levels.

00:15:50.340 --> 00:15:53.350 align:middle line:84%
And so many people had
all kinds of breakdowns.

00:15:53.350 --> 00:15:56.225 align:middle line:90%
Many people left overnight.

00:15:56.225 --> 00:15:59.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Here was this sort of
traditionally hierarchical

00:15:59.680 --> 00:16:05.290 align:middle line:84%
situation which had
put him in isolation.

00:16:05.290 --> 00:16:07.000 align:middle line:84%
So there was no one
who could give him

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:12.875 align:middle line:84%
the feedback he needed to say,
whoa, this isn't appropriate.

00:16:12.875 --> 00:16:21.370 align:middle line:84%
>> For some time, we were
in almost a holding pattern.

00:16:21.370 --> 00:16:25.720 align:middle line:84%
We weren't sure how to proceed
with our religious leadership.

00:16:25.720 --> 00:16:31.030 align:middle line:84%
We eventually did a redesign
of our administrative and

00:16:31.030 --> 00:16:32.440 align:middle line:90%
religious leadership structure.

00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:37.420 align:middle line:84%
>> We did go toward a much
more democratic structure with

00:16:37.420 --> 00:16:39.040 align:middle line:90%
an elected board.

00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:41.380 align:middle line:84%
Up until then, the board, of
course, was all appointed.

00:16:41.380 --> 00:16:47.230 align:middle line:84%
>> But the downside is that
you have a tremendous amount

00:16:47.230 --> 00:16:49.570 align:middle line:84%
of discussion that
has to take place.

00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:52.600 align:middle line:84%
Because I mean, if
you run a business,

00:16:52.600 --> 00:16:55.750 align:middle line:84%
you're really responsible for
people for eight hours a day

00:16:55.750 --> 00:16:59.710 align:middle line:84%
for that small portion of their
lives when they work for you.

00:16:59.710 --> 00:17:01.690 align:middle line:84%
If you're a place
like this, you're

00:17:01.690 --> 00:17:04.810 align:middle line:84%
responsible for
people 24 hours a day.

00:17:04.810 --> 00:17:09.369 align:middle line:84%
And not only for their economic
life and their physical life,

00:17:09.369 --> 00:17:11.230 align:middle line:90%
but for their spiritual life--

00:17:11.230 --> 00:17:15.040 align:middle line:84%
all their lives for the people
who stay for a whole lifetime.

00:17:15.040 --> 00:17:18.970 align:middle line:84%
So taking care of people and
dealing with people's problems

00:17:18.970 --> 00:17:24.819 align:middle line:84%
and issues in a way that
is inclusive and fair

00:17:24.819 --> 00:17:29.750 align:middle line:84%
requires enormous amounts of
communication and conversation.

00:17:29.750 --> 00:17:33.230 align:middle line:84%
And it actually makes
it hard to do things.

00:17:33.230 --> 00:17:37.150 align:middle line:84%
It makes it makes the running
of the organization a little bit

00:17:37.150 --> 00:17:38.620 align:middle line:90%
unwieldy, I think.

00:17:38.620 --> 00:17:42.371 align:middle line:84%
Democracy is pretty
unwieldy by its nature.

00:17:42.371 --> 00:17:44.295 align:middle line:90%
