00:17:44.295 --> 00:17:47.181 align:middle line:90%


00:17:47.181 --> 00:17:50.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Traditionally, the role of
the teacher was defined by its

00:17:50.760 --> 00:17:54.640 align:middle line:84%
lineage line and the
surrounding culture.

00:17:54.640 --> 00:17:58.110 align:middle line:84%
Recognizing that many Westerners
would not be comfortable with

00:17:58.110 --> 00:18:01.830 align:middle line:84%
importing these institutions,
three young Americans--

00:18:01.830 --> 00:18:04.830 align:middle line:84%
students of traditional
Asian teachers--

00:18:04.830 --> 00:18:08.190 align:middle line:84%
began experimenting with
doing things in new ways

00:18:08.190 --> 00:18:10.380 align:middle line:84%
when they started the
Insight Meditation

00:18:10.380 --> 00:18:15.976 align:middle line:84%
Society and its west coast
spinoff, Spirit Rock.

00:18:15.976 --> 00:18:19.880 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that helped
us a lot is that we were able

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:22.700 align:middle line:84%
to bring some of the greatest
teachers of our lineage

00:18:22.700 --> 00:18:23.900 align:middle line:90%
to America.

00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:28.250 align:middle line:84%
They blessed us, and
then they went home.

00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:33.050 align:middle line:84%
And what that did
made our community

00:18:33.050 --> 00:18:37.790 align:middle line:84%
different than the Zen
centers, or Tibetan centers,

00:18:37.790 --> 00:18:41.630 align:middle line:84%
or even Theraveda centers
where a person from Asia

00:18:41.630 --> 00:18:46.220 align:middle line:84%
came and settled here, like Zen
Master Suzuki Roshi or Chogyam

00:18:46.220 --> 00:18:48.680 align:middle line:90%
Trungpa or Rimpoche.

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:51.380 align:middle line:84%
In those communities,
what grew around

00:18:51.380 --> 00:18:55.250 align:middle line:84%
the teacher was
in many ways a bit

00:18:55.250 --> 00:18:59.930 align:middle line:84%
of a replication of
Japan or Tibet or Burma.

00:18:59.930 --> 00:19:07.180 align:middle line:84%
Our teachers came, saw the deep
practice that we were doing,

00:19:07.180 --> 00:19:11.500 align:middle line:84%
added to it, blessed us,
and then returned and said,

00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:15.765 align:middle line:84%
you have to do it
in a Western form.

00:19:15.765 --> 00:19:19.580 align:middle line:10%
>> Jack Kornfield and friends
Joseph Goldstein and Sharon

00:19:19.580 --> 00:19:25.640 align:middle line:10%
Salzberg founded Insight
Meditation Society in 1975.

00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:28.820 align:middle line:84%
All three had spent a few years
studying Buddhist meditation

00:19:28.820 --> 00:19:32.570 align:middle line:84%
in Asia, mainly in the
Theraveda tradition of Thailand

00:19:32.570 --> 00:19:34.310 align:middle line:90%
and Burma.

00:19:34.310 --> 00:19:36.830 align:middle line:84%
Because of their backgrounds
with different teachers,

00:19:36.830 --> 00:19:39.290 align:middle line:84%
they decided to do
something atypical

00:19:39.290 --> 00:19:42.920 align:middle line:84%
and not base their new retreat
center on any one teaching

00:19:42.920 --> 00:19:44.690 align:middle line:90%
lineage.

00:19:44.690 --> 00:19:47.450 align:middle line:84%
A decade later, wanting
to build both a retreat

00:19:47.450 --> 00:19:50.510 align:middle line:84%
facility and something that
would help people integrate

00:19:50.510 --> 00:19:54.890 align:middle line:84%
the Dharma in their daily lives,
Jack moved out to the Bay Area

00:19:54.890 --> 00:19:57.875 align:middle line:84%
and founded Spirit
Rock in Marin County.

00:19:57.875 --> 00:20:02.460 align:middle line:84%
>> We decided to make a center
out here in the West Coast

00:20:02.460 --> 00:20:07.400 align:middle line:84%
close to the city so that
people could come for classes

00:20:07.400 --> 00:20:10.730 align:middle line:84%
and become part of a community,
so that there wasn't an area

00:20:10.730 --> 00:20:14.120 align:middle line:84%
of life that was spiritual
and another area that wasn't.

00:20:14.120 --> 00:20:15.710 align:middle line:90%
Because it's all sacred.

00:20:15.710 --> 00:20:18.290 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, the place that
we need it as much as anything

00:20:18.290 --> 00:20:21.350 align:middle line:84%
is in our finances, or
our personal relations,

00:20:21.350 --> 00:20:24.590 align:middle line:84%
or living on this
very small planet

00:20:24.590 --> 00:20:26.900 align:middle line:90%
with so many human beings.

00:20:26.900 --> 00:20:31.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Spirit Rock has grown rapidly
from its birth on 410 acres

00:20:31.640 --> 00:20:33.890 align:middle line:90%
of undeveloped land.

00:20:33.890 --> 00:20:36.920 align:middle line:84%
A large administrative staff
keeps all the activities,

00:20:36.920 --> 00:20:39.560 align:middle line:84%
schedules, and
facilities running.

00:20:39.560 --> 00:20:44.290 align:middle line:84%
>> This was all just a field
where they grew potatoes.

00:20:44.290 --> 00:20:47.290 align:middle line:84%
>> But many Western Dharma
teachers are like Sylvia

00:20:47.290 --> 00:20:48.500 align:middle line:90%
Wetzel.

00:20:48.500 --> 00:20:51.480 align:middle line:84%
They prefer their freedom to
running even a small Dharma

00:20:51.480 --> 00:20:52.280 align:middle line:90%
center.

00:20:52.280 --> 00:20:54.450 align:middle line:84%
>> --20 centimeters
high when we got it.

00:20:54.450 --> 00:20:57.230 align:middle line:84%
>> --with all the
responsibilities that can sap

00:20:57.230 --> 00:21:00.150 align:middle line:84%
energy away from
teaching and practice.

00:21:00.150 --> 00:21:03.350 align:middle line:84%
Thanks to modern transportation,
their business cards

00:21:03.350 --> 00:21:04.240 align:middle line:90%
could read--

00:21:04.240 --> 00:21:05.670 align:middle line:90%
have Dharma, will travel.

00:21:05.670 --> 00:21:07.350 align:middle line:84%
>> This is [? Sopata, ?]
my neighbor.

00:21:07.350 --> 00:21:10.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm a so-called
traveling teacher.

00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:14.210 align:middle line:84%
I have my private
living situation here.

00:21:14.210 --> 00:21:18.470 align:middle line:84%
And there are a
couple of centers

00:21:18.470 --> 00:21:24.290 align:middle line:84%
who invite me for longer
retreats from six to 10 days.

00:21:24.290 --> 00:21:31.970 align:middle line:84%
And these centers are mostly
Buddhist ecumenical centers.

00:21:31.970 --> 00:21:35.250 align:middle line:90%
They are run by people who--

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:38.550 align:middle line:84%
