00:29:53.828 --> 00:29:57.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Reggie Ray was formerly a
professor at Naropa University

00:29:57.840 --> 00:30:02.050 align:middle line:84%
and a teacher in
Shambala International.

00:30:02.050 --> 00:30:04.450 align:middle line:84%
Reggie resigned from
both institutions

00:30:04.450 --> 00:30:08.260 align:middle line:84%
to found Dharma Ocean
in Crestone, Colorado,

00:30:08.260 --> 00:30:12.642 align:middle line:84%
overlooking the immense
and windy San Juan Valley.

00:30:12.642 --> 00:30:18.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Many people that come to the
Dharma come with a preexisting

00:30:18.520 --> 00:30:24.100 align:middle line:84%
sense of a tremendous
disempowerment as individuals.

00:30:24.100 --> 00:30:27.640 align:middle line:84%
And they are often
initially attracted--

00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:31.540 align:middle line:84%
for example, within Tibetan
Buddhism-- to the Lamas

00:30:31.540 --> 00:30:36.130 align:middle line:84%
who are presented as
being enlightened.

00:30:36.130 --> 00:30:40.180 align:middle line:84%
In other words, our
sense of disempowerment

00:30:40.180 --> 00:30:45.100 align:middle line:84%
makes us very vulnerable to
projecting onto our teachers

00:30:45.100 --> 00:30:49.000 align:middle line:84%
some kind of idealized
father that we never had.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:52.210 align:middle line:84%
Now, initially on the
path, that's necessary.

00:30:52.210 --> 00:30:54.010 align:middle line:90%
That motivates us to practice.

00:30:54.010 --> 00:30:55.370 align:middle line:90%
So it's a good thing.

00:30:55.370 --> 00:30:57.010 align:middle line:84%
But what often
happens, especially

00:30:57.010 --> 00:30:59.080 align:middle line:84%
in the Tibetan
tradition, is that people

00:30:59.080 --> 00:31:03.490 align:middle line:84%
enter into a lifelong
dependency on their Rimpoche

00:31:03.490 --> 00:31:04.990 align:middle line:90%
or their Lama.

00:31:04.990 --> 00:31:08.620 align:middle line:84%
And what I have found over
the course of my teaching

00:31:08.620 --> 00:31:13.330 align:middle line:84%
is that that lifelong dependency
makes it impossible for them

00:31:13.330 --> 00:31:15.340 align:middle line:90%
to grow in certain ways.

00:31:15.340 --> 00:31:18.610 align:middle line:84%
And it makes it impossible
for them to really enter

00:31:18.610 --> 00:31:22.576 align:middle line:90%
an adult stage of spirituality.

00:31:22.576 --> 00:31:25.470 align:middle line:90%
That's the protector up there.

00:31:25.470 --> 00:31:27.910 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that's the mountain
where the protection

00:31:27.910 --> 00:31:30.315 align:middle line:84%
energy of this whole
area is constellated.

00:31:30.315 --> 00:31:35.090 align:middle line:84%
One of the issues
that comes up is,

00:31:35.090 --> 00:31:37.810 align:middle line:90%
what about the Asian teachers?

00:31:37.810 --> 00:31:39.000 align:middle line:90%
Don't they see that?

00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:43.090 align:middle line:84%
And aren't they
interested or motivated

00:31:43.090 --> 00:31:48.840 align:middle line:84%
to unravel that or untangle
it, dismantle that Oedipal

00:31:48.840 --> 00:31:51.410 align:middle line:90%
dependency of their students?

00:31:51.410 --> 00:31:53.380 align:middle line:84%
This is a very interesting
cultural issue.

00:31:53.380 --> 00:31:58.300 align:middle line:84%
Because in Tibet, that
lifelong dependency

00:31:58.300 --> 00:32:01.240 align:middle line:90%
was cultivated with lay people.

00:32:01.240 --> 00:32:03.730 align:middle line:84%
Literally, the vista is
about 100 miles from--

00:32:03.730 --> 00:32:06.970 align:middle line:84%
If you were a layperson,
that was kind of how it was.

00:32:06.970 --> 00:32:09.130 align:middle line:84%
The problem we have
in the West is,

00:32:09.130 --> 00:32:11.650 align:middle line:84%
when many of the Asian
teachers look at Westerners,

00:32:11.650 --> 00:32:13.300 align:middle line:90%
they see lay people.

00:32:13.300 --> 00:32:16.150 align:middle line:84%
And they see people
that maybe they

00:32:16.150 --> 00:32:18.108 align:middle line:84%
feel aren't going to
practice very much,

00:32:18.108 --> 00:32:19.900 align:middle line:84%
and aren't really going
to study very much,

00:32:19.900 --> 00:32:21.610 align:middle line:84%
and aren't going to
make the journey.

00:32:21.610 --> 00:32:23.980 align:middle line:84%
So there's a kind of
toleration on the side

00:32:23.980 --> 00:32:26.980 align:middle line:84%
of the Asian teachers
of that Oedipal

00:32:26.980 --> 00:32:30.710 align:middle line:84%
dependency in a lifelong
way that reinforces it.

00:32:30.710 --> 00:32:32.189 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:32:32.189 --> 00:32:34.161 align:middle line:90%


00:32:34.161 --> 00:32:36.910 align:middle line:84%
